noneFolder.description: This is the folder for uncategorized items

noOrganizationsList.message: You do not belong to any organisations. Organisations allow you to securely share items with other users.

noTwoStepProviders.message: This account has two-step login enabled. However, none of the configured two-step providers are supported by this web browser.

duoOrganizationDesc.message: Verify with Duo Security for your organisation using the Duo Mobile app, SMS, phone call, or U2F security key.
duoOrganizationDesc.description: 'Duo Security' and 'Duo Mobile' are product names and should not be translated.

shareDesc.message: Choose an organisation that you wish to share this item with. Sharing transfers ownership of the item to the organisation. You will no longer be the direct owner of this item once it has been shared.

shareManyDesc.message: Choose an organisation that you wish to share these items with. Sharing transfers ownership of the items to the organisation. You will no longer be the direct owner of these items once they have been shared.

collectionsDesc.message: Edit the collections that this item is being shared with. Only organisation users with access to these collections will be able to see this item.

exportWarningDesc.message: This export contains your vault data in an unencrypted format. You should not store or send the exported file over insecure channels (such as email). Delete it immediately after you are done using it.

capitalize.description: Make the first letter of a work uppercase.

changeEmailDesc.message: We have emailed a verification code to $EMAIL$. Please check your email for this code and enter it below to finalise the email address change.

logBackInOthersToo.message: Please log back in. If you are using other ByteGarden applications, log out and back in to those as well.

deauthorizeSessionsDesc.message: Concerned your account is logged in on another device? Proceed below to deauthorise all computers or devices that you have previously used. This security step is recommended if you previously used a public computer or accidentally saved your password on a device that isn't yours. This step will also clear all previously remembered two-step login sessions.

purgeVaultDesc.message: Proceed below to delete all items and folders in your vault. Items that belong to an organisation that you share with will not be deleted.

purgeOrgVaultDesc.message: Proceed below to delete all items in the organisation's vault.

instructionsFor.description: The title for the import tool instructions.

disableIconsDesc.message: Website icons provide a recognisable image next to each login item in your vault.

newCustomDomainDesc.message: Enter a list of domains separated by commas. Only "base" domains are allowed. Do not enter sub-domains. For example, enter "google.com" instead of "www.google.com". You can also enter "androidapp://package.name" to associate an Android app with other website domains.

twoStepLoginOrganizationDesc.message: Require two-step login for your organisation's users by configuring providers at the organisation level.

twoStepLoginRecoveryWarning.message: Enabling two-step login can permanently lock you out of your ByteGarden account. A recovery code allows you to access your account in the event that you can no longer use your normal two-step login provider (e.g. you lose your device). ByteGarden support will not be able to assist you if you lose access to your account. We recommend you write down or print the recovery code and keep it in a safe place.

alreadyPremiumFromOrg.message: You already have access to premium features because of an organisation of which you are a member.

twoStepAuthenticatorAppsRecommended.message: These apps are recommended. However, other authenticator apps will also work.

twoFactorYubikeySupportMobile.message: Mobile apps on a device with NFC capabilities or a USB port that can accept your YubiKey.

twoFactorU2fPlugInReadKey.message: Plug the security key into your computer's USB port and click the "Read key" button.

goodNews.description: ex. Good News, No Breached Accounts Found!

accountCredit.description: Financial term. In the case of ByteGarden, a positive balance means that you owe money, while a negative balance means that you have a credit (ByteGarden owes you money).

accountBalance.description: Financial term. In the case of ByteGarden, a positive balance means that you owe money, while a negative balance means that you have a credit (ByteGarden owes you money).

addCredit.description: Add more credit to your account's balance.

goPremium.description: Another way of saying "Get a premium membership"

premiumAccessDesc.message: You can add premium access to all members of your organisation for $PRICE$ /$INTERVAL$.

licenseFileDesc.message: Your licence file will be named something like $FILE_NAME$

uploadLicenseFilePremium.message: To upgrade your account to a premium membership you need to upload a valid licence file.

uploadLicenseFileOrg.message: To create an on-premises hosted organisation you need to upload a valid licence file.

newOrganizationDesc.message: Organisations allow you to share parts of your vault with others as well as manage related users for a specific entity such as a family, small team, or large company.

planDescFree.message: For testing or personal users to share with $COUNT$ other users.

planDescTeams.message: For businesses and other team organisations.

planDescEnterprise.message: For businesses and other large organisations.

organizationReadyToGo.message: Your new organisation is ready to go!

leaveOrganizationConfirmation.message: Are you sure you want to leave this organisation?

externalIdDesc.message: The external ID can be used as a reference or to link this resource to an external system such as a user directory.

inviteUserDesc.message: Invite a new user to your organisation by entering their ByteGarden account email address below. If they do not have a ByteGarden account already, they will be prompted to create a new account.

ownerDesc.message: The highest access user that can manage all aspects of your organisation.

adminDesc.message: Admins can access and manage all items, collections and users in your organisation.

userDesc.message: A regular user with access to assigned collections in your organisation.

managerDesc.message: Managers can access and manage assigned collections in your organisation.

usersNeedConfirmed.message: You have users that have accepted their invitation, but still need to be confirmed. Users will not have access to the organisation until they are confirmed.

verifyEmailFirst.message: Your account's email address must first be verified.

joinOrganizationDesc.message: You've been invited to join the organisation listed above. To accept the invitation, you need to log in or create a new ByteGarden account.

inviteAcceptedDesc.message: You can access this organisation once an administrator confirms your membership. We'll send you an email when that happens.

inviteAcceptFailed.message: Unable to accept invitation. Ask an organisation admin to send a new invitation.

deleteOrganizationDesc.message: Proceed below to delete this organisation and all associated data. Individual user accounts will remain, though they will not be associated to this organisation anymore.

deleteOrganizationWarning.message: Deleting the organisation is permanent. It cannot be undone.

organizationDeletedDesc.message: The organisation and all associated data has been deleted.

changeBillingPlan.description: A billing plan/package. For example: families, teams, enterprise, etc.

verifyBankAccountInitialDesc.message: Payment with a bank account is only available to customers in the United States. You will be required to verify your bank account. We will make two micro-deposits within the next 1-2 business days. Enter these amounts on the organisation's billing page to verify the bank account.

updateEncryptionKeyWarning.message: After updating your encryption key, you are required to log out and back in to all ByteGarden applications that you are currently using (such as the mobile app or browser extensions). Failure to log out and back in (which downloads your new encryption key) may result in data corruption. We will attempt to log you out automatically, although this may be delayed.

upgradeOrganizationDesc.message: This feature is not available for free organisations. Switch to a paid plan to unlock more features.

createOrganizationCreatePersonalAccount.message: Before creating your organisation, you first need to create a free personal account.

datePasswordUpdated.description: ex. Date this password was updated

veryWeak.description: ex. A very weak password. Scale: Very Weak -> Weak -> Good -> Strong

apiKeyWarning.message: Your API key has full access to the organisation. It should be kept secret.

oauth2ClientCredentials.description: 'OAuth 2.0' is a programming protocol. It should probably not be translated.
